# Network: Destination addresses 10.0.0.1, .2, and .3 form a directed cycle;
# 10.0.0.3 additionally has an exit to 10.0.0.4. Address 10.0.0.5 is isolated.
# Policy: Union provides the cycle edges and the nondeterministic exit.
# Topology: id; each policy execution is one logical forwarding edge.
# Property cycle-to-exit: A packet can circle and then choose the exit.
# Property second-back-to-first: The cycle allows 10.0.0.2 to reach 10.0.0.1.
# Property exit-back-to-cycle: The exit is a sink and cannot return.
# Property cycle-self: Reflexivity and the nonempty cycle both reach the starting address.
# Property isolated: The cycle cannot reach 10.0.0.5.
policy =
    (filter(dst_ip = 10.0.0.1) . dst_ip <- 10.0.0.2)
  + (filter(dst_ip = 10.0.0.2) . dst_ip <- 10.0.0.3)
  + (filter(dst_ip = 10.0.0.3) . dst_ip <- 10.0.0.1)
  + (filter(dst_ip = 10.0.0.3) . dst_ip <- 10.0.0.4);
topology = id;
check cycle-to-exit: dst_ip = 10.0.0.1 => dst_ip = 10.0.0.4;
check second-back-to-first: dst_ip = 10.0.0.2 => dst_ip = 10.0.0.1;
check exit-back-to-cycle: dst_ip = 10.0.0.4 => dst_ip = 10.0.0.2;
check cycle-self: dst_ip = 10.0.0.1 => dst_ip = 10.0.0.1;
check isolated: dst_ip = 10.0.0.1 => dst_ip = 10.0.0.5;
